BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
To isolate the variable [`a\text{,}`] we need to divide each side by [`-17`] (because [`a`] is _multiplied_ by [`-17`]).

[```\newcommand{\divideunder}[2]{\frac{#1}{{\highlight{{#2}}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
51\amp=-17a\\
\divideunder{51}{-17}\amp=\divideunder{-17a}{-17}\\
-3\amp=a
\end{aligned}
```]

We should check the solution by substituting [`-3`] in for [`a`] in the original equation:

[```\newcommand{\substitute}[1]{{\color{blue}{{#1}}}}\newcommand{\confirm}[1]{\stackrel{\checkmark}{#1}}\newcommand{\wonder}[1]{\stackrel{\text{?}}{#1}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
51\amp=-17a\\
51\amp\wonder{=}-17(\substitute{-3})\\
51\amp\confirm{=}51
\end{aligned}
```]

The solution [`-3`] is checked, and the solution set is [`\{-3\}\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

